node.title: Victoria records 1,290 new COVID-19 cases and two deaths
node.alt: A staff member in COVID-19 protective gear putting a nasal swap in a visitors nose.
node.description: There are now 11,649 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 599 people have died in the current outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,290\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and two\u00a0deaths.", "There are now 11,649\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 599\u00a0people have died in the current outbreak.", "There are 323\u00a0people in hospital with COVID-19, of whom 77\u00a0are in intensive care, and 40\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 39\u00a0people were in ICU but their infections were no longer considered active.", "The new cases were identified from 55,122\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 3,266\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
